# Ontario Readiness Sync (mandatory)

**Owner requirement: 100% parity** between live HTML and markdown companions (facts, structure, links). See **`.cursor/rules/diligence-100-percent-parity.mdc`** and **`AGENT-HANDOVER.md` Rule #3**.

When you change **any** of: Ontario features, readiness scores, phase status, provincial desks, diligence layout, nav links, or pages linked from `/ontario-readiness` or `/strategic-partner-letter` — update **every** companion in the same session before finishing.

## Canonical source

**`/ontario-readiness`** (`ontario-readiness.html`) is the score and phase truth. Written companion: `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-READINESS-REPORT.md`.

## Companion set (all must match — 100% parity)

| Live page | Written companion |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `/ontario-readiness` | `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-READINESS-REPORT.md` |
| `/strategic-partner-letter` | `docs/strategic-partner/STRATEGIC-PARTNER-LETTER-2026-06.md` |
| `/valuation-equity-structure` | `docs/strategic-partner/VALUATION-AND-EQUITY-STRUCTURE.md` |
| `/term-sheet` | `docs/strategic-partner/TERM-SHEET-SEED-PREFERRED-SHARE.md` |
| `/project-plan` | `docs/strategic-partner/STRATEGIC-PARTNER-PROJECT-PLAN.md` |
| `/revenue-projection` | `docs/strategic-partner/REVENUE-AND-NET-INCOME-PROJECTION.md` |
| `/capabilities` | `docs/MEDIFORGE-CAPABILITIES-GUIDE.md` |
| `/evidence-binder` | `docs/PHASE-*-COMPLETION.md` rows it cites |
| `/ontario-self-assessment` | `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-SPEC-TRACEABILITY.md` |
| Scores/gaps | `docs/ONTARIOMD-GAP-REPORT.md`, `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md` |
| Staff workflows | `user-manual.html` ↔ `docs/USER-MANUAL.md` |
| Handover | `AGENT-HANDOVER.md` session log |

Also sync: `docs/MEDIFORGE-AT-A-GLANCE.md`, `docs/ONTARIOMD-READINESS-PLAN.md`, `capabilities.html` compare table rows that cite readiness %.

**Financial companions** must agree on every shared seed term and cross-link `/financial-model` where they link project plan / revenue / term sheet. `npm run check:ontario-readiness` enforces key terms and required links.

## Before you finish a session

1. Run `npm run check:ontario-readiness` (scores, terms, required links — not full prose parity).
2. **Spot-check 100% parity:** HTML ↔ markdown side by side for every pair you touched.
3. Run full `npm run check` if promoting to production.
4. Update `AGENT-HANDOVER.md` session log + **Last updated**.
5. If overall score changes: edit `CANONICAL` in `scripts/check-ontario-readiness-sync.mjs` to match `ontario-readiness.html`.

## Never

- Never use "investor" or "investors" in Ontario companion pages: use **Strategic Partner** / **Strategic Partners**.
- Ship code that touches provincial/Ontario UI without updating linked HTML pages and their markdown companions.
- Leave `70–80%` (or older bands) as **overall** readiness on any companion when canonical is `72–82%`.
- Update only one page in the set because "it was a small fix."
- Stop at "guard passed" when prose structure or links still differ between HTML and markdown.
